title: Augustine to Galileo - The History of Science.pdf
description:
Falcon Press | 1952 | Pdf | Eng | 436 pag | 42.4 MB

A. C. CROMBIE - University Lecturer in the History of Science, Oxford

In the author's view, one system of scientific thought gives place to another not necessarily because men discover fresh facts which make the old theories obsolete but often because, for some reason, they begin to look at long familiar evidence in a new way
